  "market_context": "Week of April 22–26, 2024; low-news environment awaiting economic data. Price formed a multi-day broadening pattern where Asia/London sessions swept one side of the range, then price expanded to the opposite side, consistent with seek-and-destroy profile behavior.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the lower side of the range into a fair value gap, then moved decisively to the upper side of the expanding range—confirming the broadening formation as a higher-time-frame structure.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a recent multi-day broadening formation on the NQ 15-minute chart, marked by alternating sweeps of range extremes (lows then highs).",
    "Step 2: Noted that price swept the lower side of the range into a gap (FVG), triggering a move toward the opposite (upper) side of the expanding range.",
    "Step 3: Highlighted equal highs at the upper boundary as buy-side liquidity, anticipating price would target that zone after the lower sweep.",
    "Step 4: Confirmed the pattern aligns with ICT's 'seek and destroy' daily profile when waiting for news, where both Asia high/low are taken before directional expansion."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Broadening formations signal expanding volatility and liquidity targeting; after sweeping one side (especially into a gap), price often moves to the opposite extreme. This is a structural clue—not a direct entry—but informs draw-on-liquidity and bias.",
